    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2010-07-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2010-09-03T21:37:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Outer Continental Shelf Lands Act to require the operator of a drilling and production operation under a lease to submit annually to the Secretary of the Interior a specified certification by the operator's chief executive officer that the operator is in compliance with all pertinent laws and operating regulations.</p> <p>Subjects the chief executive officer to a civil penalty for non-compliance with this requirement.<br> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Outer Continental Shelf Lands Act to require the chief executive officer of each drilling and production operation under a lease under that Act to annually certify the operator's compliance with all applicable laws and operating regulations.</title>
